\begin_body

\begin_layout Title
EPIB 613 Introduction to Statistical Software (Fall 2018)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
DESCRIPTION: The course is to introduce the statistical software 
\family typewriter
R
\family default
, a free environment for statistical computing and graphics, to graduate
 students in the MSc and MScPH degree programs in the Department of Epidemiology
 and Biostatistics.
 It can help students to get familiar with basic commands for managing and
 analyzing data in 
\family typewriter
R
\family default
.
 This course provides hands-on experiences of using 
\family typewriter
R
\family default
 with various data formats to cover the basics of data creation and manipulation
, graphics, and elementary statistical analysis.
 By the end of this course, participants should be able to use 
\family typewriter
R
\family default
 for data mining, statistical analyses including descriptive analysis, statistic
al inference, and reporting.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
LOCATION: Education Building 437
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
DAY/TIME: Thursday, 11:35 AM - 12:55 PM
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
FORMAT: Approximately 1.5 hours including lectures and hands-on practice
 each week in the computer lab.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
ADMISSIBILITY: This course is open to Epidemiology MSc, MSc Public Health,
 and PhD (epi) degree students concurrently enrolled in EPIB601.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
GRADING: Pass/Fail based on class participation and assignments
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
ASSIGNMENTS: There will be 3 assignments in total.
 Each assignment will be an 
\family typewriter
R
\family default
 exercise based on materials covered in class.
 Assignments should be submitted through 
\shape italic
myCourses
\shape default
 in PDF format by 5 PM on each assignment’s due date.
 Late assignments will be penalized by 10% per day unless an extension has
 been granted by the instructor or in the case of an emergency.
\end_layout

